              <h3>Caleb</h3>
              <p>Cider vinegar. Molasses. Ceylon cinnamon. Ancho chiles. Mexican oregano. Flat-leaf parsley. More flat-leaf parsley. Okay, just a little more parsley… Perfect! Creating and sharing healthy and (usually) delicious food is a deep passion of mine. I love to explore and experience rich flavors and aromas, whether that’s coming from home-cooked meals, craft beer, or cocktails. As is the case for cooking and mixology, I believe that balance is one of the keys to a fulfilling life.</p>
              <p>Much aligned with my musical tastes, I love to cook with complex and aggressive flavors from every corner of the globe. I assert that every dish should include a healthy pinch of cayenne… or two… preferably homegrown ;). I’m grateful to find myself tromping around wetlands and forests (and the occasional cubicle) as my day job. I’m a huge nature nerd and animal lover, and I strive to walk the walk when it comes to sustainable and healthy living \m/</p>
